 A Doctor can prescribe one or more Drugs for several Patients
- A Patient can obtain prescriptions from several Doctors
- Every Patient has a Primary Physician
- Every Doctor has at least one Patient
- A Pharmaceutical Company can have several Contracts with different Pharmacies
- A Pharmacy can sell several Drugs at different prices
- A Drug is sold by a given Pharmaceutical Company, and the Trade Name identifies a drug uniquely from among the products of that company
- Each Prescription has a Date and a Quantity associated with it
- A Pharmaceutical Company can contract with several Pharmaceutical Companies
- A Pharmacy appoints a Supervisor for each Contract
